 Queenstown - Police in Queenstown are searching for the mother of a one-day old baby boy, who was found dumped near the bushes at Westborne township on Thursday at about 13:00. "It is alleged that the child was seen by a passerby, who alerted the police," said police spokesperson, Captain Namhla Mdleleni. "Police arrived at the scene and they find the child still alive. 'The baby was taken to Frontier Hospital for examination and for place of safety and he is still in good condition." Police are appealing to anyone who can assist with the whereabouts of the mother of the child can please contact Queenstown Police at 045 8086029  or toll free number 086001011. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 